    "text": "Team Operations\nFind ownership guidance for team setup, roster, schedule, config, analytics, and admin workflows.\nHelp - Team Operations ← Back to Help Portal Team Operations Ownership model for team creation, roster, schedule, and configuration. Team Creation and Core Management Coach/Admin: Create and manage teams from dashboard.html . Coach/Admin: Edit team metadata in edit-team.html . Parent/Member: View team context in team.html only. Roster and Schedule Ownership Coach/Admin: Manage roster in edit-roster.html . Coach/Admin: Plan/update events in edit-schedule.html . Coach/Admin: Maintain an officials directory in edit-schedule.html for future game officiating assignments. Officials are separate from roster members, parents, coaches, and generic game assignments. Parent/Member: Consume schedule from team.html and calendar.html . Parent: Revoke household contact access from Parent Dashboard — marks the contact's membership revoked, removes delegated parent/player links, and invalidates related invite tokens. Config and Analytics Controls Coach/Admin: Stat and config management in edit-config.html . Stat setup controls include visibility, scope, format, precision, ranking, formula, group, and Top Stat selection. Stats marked as public leaderboard Top Stats must have public-player visibility. Coach/Admin: Team planning workflows in game-plan.html and drills.html . Parent: Parent-specific team and player views in parent-dashboard.html and player.html . Administration Admin: Global admin workflows in admin tools . Admin: Access checks and status verification through admin tooling pages.\nHelp - Team Operations\n← Back to Help Portal\nTeam Operations\nOwnership model for team creation, roster, schedule, and configuration.\nTeam Creation and Core Management\n- Coach/Admin: Create and manage teams from dashboard.html .\n- Coach/Admin: Edit team metadata in edit-team.html .\n- Parent/Member: View team context in team.html only.\nRoster and Schedule Ownership\n- Coach/Admin: Manage roster in edit-roster.html .\n- Coach/Admin: Plan/update events in edit-schedule.html .\n- Coach/Admin: Maintain an officials directory in edit-schedule.html for future game officiating assignments. Officials are separate from roster members, parents, coaches, and generic game assignments.\n- Parent/Member: Consume schedule from team.html and calendar.html .\n- Parent: Revoke household contact access from Parent Dashboard — marks the contact's membership revoked, removes delegated parent/player links, and invalidates related invite tokens.\nConfig and Analytics Controls\n- Coach/Admin: Stat and config management in edit-config.html . Stat setup controls include visibility, scope, format, precision, ranking, formula, group, and Top Stat selection. Stats marked as public leaderboard Top Stats must have public-player visibility.\n- Coach/Admin: Team planning workflows in game-plan.html and drills.html .\n- Parent: Parent-specific team and player views in parent-dashboard.html and player.html .\nAdministration\n- Admin: Global admin workflows in admin tools .\n- Admin: Access checks and status verification through admin tooling pages."
